nd you are uncertain of its accuracy. Note any verified or refuted claims in your comments.\n./data/evaluation_prompt.md:38:**Screenshots**: If screenshot images are attached, analyze them visually. Evaluate what is shown on screen — code quality, UI output, errors, terminal output, etc. Cross-reference what you see in the screenshots with claims made in the conversation or transcript.\n./data/evaluation_prompt.md:62:\"transcriptionQuality\": {\n./data/evaluation_prompt.md:123:Evaluate verbal communication effectiveness based on the provided transcript content, accounting for potential transcription abnormalities.\n./data/evaluation_prompt.md:127:- **Clarity of Expression** (0-2): How clearly were ideas articulated based on the transcription?\n./data/evaluation_prompt.md:128:- **Technical Communication** (0-2): Effective explanation of concepts, adjusting for any mis-transcriptions?\n./data/evaluation_prompt.md:133:**Adjustments**: If the transcript content has errors (e.g., garbled text due to AI inaccuracies, accents, or noise), deduct points only for candidate-caused issues (e.g., mumbling), not technical transcription failures. If the transcript is empty or unclear, note as an abnormality and score conservatively.\n./data/evaluation_prompt.md:150:• [Patterns or insights, e.g., 'Handled transcription abnormalities well by providing clear screenshots']\n./data/evaluation_prompt.md:167:_This refined framework ensures precise, fair evaluation by addressing input abnormalities and providing structured, evidence-based scoring._\n./data/evaluations.json:1:[{\"id\":\"dee3cfb2-7732-4864-a9d8-0fa015604cb9\",\"evaluation\":\"### Evaluation\\n\\n#### 1. Helper Bot Conversation Quality (Weight: 30%)\\n\\n**Score: 8/10**\\n\\n- **Question Relevance and Specificity (2/2)**: The candidate's questions were directly aligned with the task requirements, showing a clear understanding of the objectives.\\n- **Engagement Depth (1/2)**: The candidate did not probe deeply on some respon